pageContext.claim: “In Wayne County, that's a great one. That's Detroit. One hundred and seventy-four thousand ballots were counted without being tied to an actual registered voter. Nobody knows where they came from.”
pageContext.analysis: This claim by Trump is false, according to The Detroit Free Press. Texas Attorney General Ken Paxton, in a lawsuit that was dismissed by the U.S. Supreme Court, sought to overturn Michigan's certified election results by using a flawed analysis that would have had the justices believe that all 174,384 absentee ballots cast in Detroit were invalid. The analysis misinterpreted the report of precinct-level results for Wayne County. The absentee ballots that were counted in Detroit were ones that had already been verified as coming from eligible voters before they were counted.
